{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"deserving-cloistered-tayra","description":"## What\n\nExtend `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/code-review-tests.md` (the Pass-1 test-sufficiency overlay) with the two meaningful antipatterns the current rubric does not name, each paired with explicit false-positive guards so the addition catches real deficiencies without nits or over-firing. No front-matter, posture, threshold, or routing change (the criterion stays advisory; `src/rebar/llm/code_review/criteria_routing.json` untouched).\n\nAntipatterns to add to the FLAG list:\n- **non-gating test**: a new/changed test that silently skips or non-strict-xfails under the supported CI environment — the test provides no regression protection because it never runs where it gates. Guards: a skip guarding a genuinely optional platform/dependency that the supported CI environment DOES exercise is NOT a finding; a strict xfail (`strict=True`) tied to a stated removal condition is NOT a finding; do not demand proof of collection for ordinarily-discoverable tests (only flag when the skip/xfail condition is visible in the diff and would hold in CI).\n- **unrealistic fault injection / sleep-only synchronization**: (a) a recovery/cleanup/rollback path 'tested' by injecting the fault OUTSIDE the seam under test (e.g. replacing the top-level command with a raiser when the contract is mid-operation rollback), so the recovery code never executes; (b) a concurrency/race test whose primary synchronization is a timing sleep. Guards: a fault injected at the real boundary (monkeypatching the actual failing call at the point the contract covers) is VALID; a short sleep used as a secondary settling wait alongside a deterministic primary mechanism (barrier, pipe, marker file, event) is NOT a finding.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/code-review-tests.md` names both antipatterns in the FLAG list and both guard sets in the false-positive-guards section, phrased consistently with the existing rubric (litmus-style, evidence-record contract unchanged).\n- [ ] Front-matter unchanged; `python -m rebar.llm.prompting.prompts regenerate-index` (or the legacy module path) produces no diff in `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/index.json`.\n- [ ] No change to `criteria_routing.json` or any threshold/posture.\n- [ ] `make lint` passes and the code-review prompt/eval unit tests still pass (`pytest tests/unit/test_code_review_evals.py tests/unit/test_code_review_fp_ledger.py`).","id":"e8d3-03b6-cf2d-46ae","parent_id":"e8ed-aec2-3337-4244","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"code-review tests criterion: flag non-gating tests and unrealistic fault injection (with FP guards)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783883964683636001,"uuid":"c83b685e-387d-48a2-944e-53eef9642676"}